    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3844581320" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3844581320" />
    <a title="Rachel" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/38218294-rachel"><img alt="Rachel" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1577929592p2/38218294.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3844581320?book_show_action=true">Feb 19, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rachel" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rachel" href="/user/show/38218294-rachel">Rachel</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781984804907" href="/book/show/41769547-blood-brothers">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3844581320" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7949284197270728297">Blood Brothers, book one of Nora Roberts, the Sign of Seven trilogy, pulls you in and doesn’t let go. While the battle of good vs evil is expected, it’s more the messaging behind it that struck me in this story. It’s the choices we make everyday on how we choose to live, what we open ourselves up to, and how we choose to protect ourselves mentally, emotionally, and spiritually, or not, that define us. It is not major choices or big, epic situations that define if we are good people or not, it’s </span>
  <span id="freeText7949284197270728297" style="display:none">Blood Brothers, book one of Nora Roberts, the Sign of Seven trilogy, pulls you in and doesn’t let go. While the battle of good vs evil is expected, it’s more the messaging behind it that struck me in this story. It’s the choices we make everyday on how we choose to live, what we open ourselves up to, and how we choose to protect ourselves mentally, emotionally, and spiritually, or not, that define us. It is not major choices or big, epic situations that define if we are good people or not, it’s the choices we make everyday that push up up or down on that continuum. The choices that follow a path in one direction or another, some made deliberately and others from a series of small slides and glides. It may be the timing of reading it now, but the message under the story has even more appeal to me than the story, which is the NR gold standard itself.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7949284197270728297" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


